//download nagios using docker
docker pull jasonrivers/nagios:latest
docker start -ai nagios4 OR
ocker run --name nagiosdemo -p 8888:80 jasonrivers/nagios:latest

Open the Nagios Webui on port 8888. =>(Type  localhost:8888)
Enter username : nagiosadmin 
Enter password : nagios
It shows localhost. Now click on localhost

If we observe the docker containers in DockerHub, we can see the latest Nagios Installed running on port:8888


1. Navigate to the Host Information Page:
Select a host from the Hosts menu
2. oHost Status: Indicates if the system is UP or DOWN.
 Metrics: View CPU usage, memory status, and network activity.

